# GSD Workflows and Planning Context

This project uses **GSD (Get Shit Done)** workflows and a **.planning** folder. Use them for project setup, planning, and execution.

## Where Things Live

- **Workflows**: `.agent/workflows/*.md` — step-by-step procedures (read the relevant workflow first when the user asks for GSD actions).
- **Project state**: `.planning/` — vision, roadmap, requirements, phase plans, codebase map.

## When to Use What

| User intent | Do this |
|-------------|--------|
| Status / what's next | Run `/gsd-progress` — read `.agent/workflows/gsd-progress.md`, then `node rules/get-shit-done/bin/gsd-tools.cjs init progress --include state,roadmap,project,config` and summarize. |
| Plan a phase | Read `.agent/workflows/gsd-plan-phase.md`, run `gsd-tools.cjs init plan-phase <N>`, create/update PLAN.md in `.planning/phases/`. |
| Execute a phase | Read `.agent/workflows/gsd-execute-phase.md`, load phase context, run plans by waves. |
| New project / milestone | Read `.agent/workflows/gsd-new-project.md`; create/update PROJECT.md, REQUIREMENTS.md, ROADMAP.md, STATE.md in `.planning/`. |
| Map codebase | Read `.agent/workflows/gsd-map-codebase.md`; write STACK, ARCHITECTURE, etc. into `.planning/codebase/`. |
| Help / commands | Read `.agent/workflows/gsd-help.md` and show the command reference. |

## Planning Context to Load

When doing GSD or project tasks, load as needed:

- **Vision & scope**: `.planning/PROJECT.md`
- **Requirements**: `.planning/REQUIREMENTS.md`
- **Phases & progress**: `.planning/ROADMAP.md`, `.planning/STATE.md`
- **Config**: `.planning/config.json` (mode, depth, parallelization)
- **Codebase map**: `.planning/codebase/*.md` (ARCHITECTURE, STACK, STRUCTURE, etc.)
- **Current phase**: `.planning/phases/<phase-name>/` (PLAN.md, SUMMARY.md, VERIFICATION.md)

## GSD Tools

All workflows use:

```bash
node rules/get-shit-done/bin/gsd-tools.cjs <command> [args]
```

Examples: `init new-project`, `init plan-phase 1`, `init execute-phase 1`, `init progress`, `commit "message" --files <paths>`.

Always read the relevant workflow file from `.agent/workflows/` before executing a GSD command so you follow the full procedure.
